name: CDD
de: Changes the current working directory
see: CD DIR RD MD PUSHD
req: CMD_CDD

SYNOPSIS:
<OL>
<LI>
EBNF: CDD 
<LI>
EBNF: CDD [ drive ':' ] path
<LI>
EBNF: CDD '-'
</OL>

The behaviour of <CMD>CDD</CMD> is similiar to the <CMD>CD</CMD>
command, but it always changes both the currently selected drive and
the current directory, thus, it changes the current working directory.

<P>For further details please see the <CMD>CD</CMD> command.
